Class HashMap2<K1,K2,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<Tuple2<K1,K2>,V>
        • common.dataStructures.HashMap2<K1,K2,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K1 - - the first key type
    K2 - - the second key type
    V - - the value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<Tuple2<K1,K2>,V>

    public class HashMap2<K1,K2,V>
extends java.util.HashMap<Tuple2<K1,K2>,V>
    A HashMap from the given two key values to a value type Each key can be present more than once, as it takes a pair of key values to map to a single value.

    Uses Tuple2 internally to manage key pairs.
    Author:
    Mshnik
